<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">All four paths end with one completed AI Documentation Template + one AI-source OPVL. The path you pick is about how you want to use AI on your topic.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I can OPVL an AI source on my dossier topic AND complete the AI Documentation Template — including the "one thing the AI got wrong" field with specificity.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Standard — Gemini on my topic</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Ask Gemini your dossier topic question. Save the conversation. OPVL the response. Fill out the full AI Documentation Template.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Compare two AIs on the same question</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Ask Gemini and Claude the same dossier question. OPVL each response separately. Document both. Highlight where they disagree — that's gold for the synthesis section.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Push back with The Skeptic</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Ask The Skeptic to challenge one of your traditional sources' claims. Notice what counter-evidence it surfaces. Document the exchange + OPVL the Skeptic's pushback.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Practice</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">D</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Synthesis-first (for students with AI source already done)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If you already have your AI source from outside class, spend the block on cross-source synthesis — write the section comparing where your three sources agree and where they disagree.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Choice</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

